Following is a sample script for a Perl script that reads the file and prints the number of occurrences of each word:
```
#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
my $file = "file.txt";
open(my $fh, '<', $file) or die "Could not open file '$file' $!";
my %word_counts;
while (my $line = <$fh>) {
    chomp($line);
    my @words = split(/\s+/, $line);
    foreach my $word (@words) {
        $word_counts{$word}++;
    }
}
foreach my $word (keys %word_counts) {
    print "$word: $word_counts{$word}\n";
}
close($fh); ### or use close($fh) if you want to keep the file open after the script finishes running. ###
